Title : List of crossings of the River Wye
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}
[[File:Map of the River Wye (West Midlands and Wales, UK).jpeg|thumb|300px|River Wye]]

'''Crossings of the [[River Wye]]''' in the [[United Kingdom|UK]] cover the whole length of the {{convert|215|km|mi}} from its source to the [[River Severn]]. For much of its length the river forms part of [[Wales-England border|the border]] between England and [[Wales]]. The lower [[Wye Valley]] is an [[Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Natural England information on AONBs and map | work=Natural England | url=http://www.naturalengland.org.uk/ourwork/conservation/designations/aonb/default.aspx | accessdate=2012-10-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Natural England information on Wye Valley AONB| work=Natural England| url=http://www.naturalengland.org.uk/ourwork/conservation/designations/aonb/wyevalley.aspx| accessdate=2012-10-05| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140830064435/http://www.naturalengland.org.uk/ourwork/conservation/designations/aonb/wyevalley.aspx| archivedate=30 August 2014| df=dmy-all}}</ref> There are some 15 Grade II [[Listed building|listed bridges]], just 1 Grade II* listed bridge and 3 Grade I listed bridges.

