|Severn-Wye Cable Tunnel 
|{{Coord|51.61098|-2.66921|region:GB_type:landmark|name=Severn-Wye Cable Tunnel}}
|
!-
|[[Beachley]] – [[Aust]]
|The tunnel is 47.5 m deep, with a diameter of 3.05 m and a total length of 3,678 m.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://business.highbeam.com/411917/article-1G1-135814115/mono-severn-wye-tunnel-project-wins-award|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121011142151/http://business.highbeam.com/411917/article-1G1-135814115/mono-severn-wye-tunnel-project-wins-award|dead-url= yes|archive-date= 11 October 2012|publisher= [[HighBeam Research|HighBeam]]|title= Mono Severn Wye Tunnel Project wins award.|accessdate=10 May 2011}}</ref> The tunnel carries two 400 kV circuits, each with three cables.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.convertingtoday.co.uk/story.asp?sectioncode=12&storycode=32816 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110728021227/http://www.convertingtoday.co.uk/story.asp?sectioncode=12&storycode=32816 |dead-url= yes |archive-date= 28 July 2011 |publisher= Global Trade Media|title= Severn-Wye Cable Tunnel refurb |accessdate=10 May 2011}} </ref> The tunnel is owned by [[Npower (UK)|npower]]. The image to the right shows the cables on pylons entering the Aust (eastern) end of the tunnel before going underground.   
|
|[[File:Pylons - geograph.org.uk - 190588.jpg|120px]]
|-
|[[Aust Severn Powerline Crossing]]
|{{Coord|51.60578|-2.64136|region:GB_type:landmark|name=Aust Severn Powerline Crossing}}
|
!-
|
|Longest powerline span in the UK at 1 mile (1,618 metres).
